reviews.review_text: Have to say, was PLEASANTLY surprised today when we visited this location. Waited a little bit at drive through to order, and team member was very apologetic. When we waited for our food for a very short period of time, again, very apologetic and provided a couple of items for free. We typically visit the Fleetwood location, which is horrible.  The location in Cloverdale is totally worth the trip.  Order was perfect and service was top notch. Our new favourite choice.

I normally wouldn t write a review for mcdonald s because they re all pretty much the same, but I just wanted to leave one for one lady that works the drive thru. I ve been going through an emotional time the past few days because of my dog being very sick, & even though she has no idea, she has been such a ray of sunshine & has made my day. I went through the drive thru twice in the past few days to get a drink because it s near the vet clinic my dog s been at & both times she has been absolutely lovely. I don t know her name, but today she was wearing some blue gloves underneath the plastic latex gloves that all the staff wear. Both today & Monday (both times ~10am) she was at the second window as well. Please let her know that she is wonderful & her kindness has meant the world to me

My family and I come to this location quite often and always use the drive though. We have always had such wonderful experiences when we are served by Sheryl. Her amazing attitude and commitment to her customers is remarkable. We have always said how much we love it when she serves us. You are very lucky to have her
Everythings great. But they are closed everyday between 3 &4 am

Fast and accurate drive through, especially on mornings when there s a sweet lady working at the last window, she s got shorter curly hair and she s always so friendly and always double checks everything. I don t know her name but she seems to be there weekday mornings and she s the best! I do wish McDonalds offered more dairy free options, I would happily pay more and likely order more coffees etc if they didn t upset my stomach like regular lactose/dairy does.

Washroom is very small, only one stall for a man. Kiosks are too closely together, I felt cramped. Seating is fine. Staff are quite nice, customer service is good. Shopping is quite good outside,  the reason I go to this McDonalds.
Very consistant food and service

This is my local McDonalds on a busy intersection a few kms from my home.  When cv19 hit I was really big and decided to intermittent fast and choose a keto designed lifestyle.  I never drank coffee before but now needed to due to my fasting. So each day 5 days a week around 6:30am I drive to order my xtra large coffee for 2.40$ and get a couple butters to put into it which helps me stave off hunger till I break my fast at 11am. The staff is amazing and I always collect the tiny sticker to get my almost free xtra large on the 8th visit. I should double dip on the points I havent yet maybe I will do so soon. Staff is great, quick and look forward to a smile and a have a great day...it is almost like Im harkened back to Mulberry in the 50s they are so nice.

Went there late at night/early in the morning (depending on your perspective), dude named Nathan, looked kinda funny and was a bit short, made my meal lickity split, gave him a fist bump and a kiss on the cheek. Best Customer Service Ever!!!!

Waited a long time in line due to another customer getting refunds etc  ...when we got to our turn the manager apologized to which we said..no problem at all . After we finished ordering our meals the manager said it was on her ! Totally unexpected and very well done...thank you !!

As we all know McDonalds food is pretty much the same everywhere, however I give this location a 5 due to the consistency over the past couple years of the morning crew in their great service. Over the past couple years even though my visits could be sometimes a few weeks apart the drive thru always moves quickly when getting coffee never having to wait for so long unlike some other locations. Its always the same morning crew who are courteous, and efficient in moving customers through the line up which means they are organized in the kitchen, and have a great team leader. If you are in a hurry in the morning but need that coffee/quick breakfast this location is perfect. You dont have to wait as if they are cooking a Thanksgiving turkey.
Friendly staff, everything you see is super cleaned, maybe this is the cleanest mcdonalds. Food is hot, good and delicious. Fast service too.

This is the best McDonald s to go to for late night and middle of the night in the area. The manager is quick and efficient she makes fresh fries every time and doesn t skimp on sauces. I specifically drive to this one over any others in Surrey/Langley.

So, here I am, once again reviewing a McDonalds... but... Im actually recommending this one this time! I feel like this should go against my code...however hear me out! Their egg McMuffins...are actually made with a freshly cracked egg...and at this particular McDonalds...they cook them to PERFECTION!! Its got the slightest bit of runny yolk left, sausage cooked without being burned or rubbery and the cheese is actually tasty! All this however pales in comparison to the cheery, smiley, joyful ladies who greet you on the microphone, take your order, send you ahead, and then with a smile so big that can be seen through their mask, hand you a breakfast that tastes so good, it can only be because it was crafted with love.... Im LOVING IT XD

I went threw the drive thru and forgot to order a side of tarter sauce so added it at the first window. They didnt forget it and it was in the bag with a straw and napkins. Thank you. So many times i go threw other McDonalds and most of the time my bag is  missing something. I still check the bag before i pull away from the window just incase.
Its McDonalds. Always consistent no matter the location. Docked the food because they didnt have any breakfast burritos. Parking: Right outside the door. Good for us seniors.
